summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsCruelty FreeVeganSustainable PackagingGive BackNUDESTIX's NUDIES MATTE All Over Face Bronze Color is a multi-tasking balm to create warm bronzing on face, eyes, and lips for an easy #gonudebutbetter look. It includes a convenient, removable blending brush for applying on-the-go!

reviews.headline: Moldy cheese smell
reviews.comments: Upon first use I was gagged with the smell of sour moldy cheese. Is this normal? Should I be concerned about putting this on my face? Did I receive a bad/expired batch. What is going on Ulta and Nudestix!!!!

reviews.headline: Lovely Shade
reviews.comments: I usually stick with neutral blush/makeup shades but wanted something with more pop for summer. I picked up the color Picante. Its the perfect orange, red shade. It leans more orange than red which i though might not work for my skin tone (light, neutral) but you can blend it out or build it up depending on how much color you want. Feels great on my skin, too. Im glad i took a chance on this one!!!

reviews.headline: Pretty
reviews.comments: Pretty. If you do just 1 layer and dab on with the attached brush, it looks like a natural flush on the cheeks. Do 2 layers for a more intense color. Can also swipe on the lips/ lids for a matchy-matchy look. As someone who has dry skin/ prefers a more neutral toned blush, Yes i would recommend. Did not mess up the concealer i had layered underneath it to cover acne.

reviews.headline: Cream blush
reviews.comments: Love the color definitely bubble gum

reviews.headline: My new go to blush
reviews.comments: I am so thankful I found this NUDESTIX blush! I purchased the Naughty N'Spice color and it's PERFECT with my naturally tan skin. The built in brush just blends it right in and you can build it up if you want more color. I have used it as a lip color as well which is equally gorgeous. This is a staple for me and I will be purchasing another.

reviews.headline: Love Love love bubba
reviews.comments: The perfect bubba-licious shade this bubble gum pink gives me just the right pop of colour for day-today wear  then I  can go in and have it built up if I want to ignore my blush blindness and go full glam. Would definitely repurchase and recommend to friends.

reviews.headline: New Fave Summer Shade
reviews.comments: Kevin's New Shade BUBBA is my favourite! IT's the perfect pop of bubblegum pink. For all the Blush Bling girlies :)

reviews.headline: SO Patchy!
reviews.comments: I wanted to love it, I got it on sale and the color is super pretty, but its so patchy no matter how I apply. Not long lasting (even for a cream blush), not very creamy, again SO hard to blend and if you use it straight on your face it takes the makeup off underneath

reviews.headline: SO Patchy!
reviews.comments: I wanted to love it, I got it on sale and the color is super pretty, but its so patchy no matter how I apply. Not long lasting (even for a cream blush), not very creamy, again SO hard to blend and if you use it straight on your face it takes the makeup off underneath

reviews.headline: Love Bubba!
reviews.comments: Love this blush! It adds a beautiful pop of color to the eyes, cheeks and lips! Love the formula and ease of use of this product. The BUBBA shade is my favourite!

reviews.headline: Yes but no
reviews.comments: Great product. Just wouldn't repurchase again. Really tired of the hyper sexual names of makeup products. I have a daughter. I don't want her to read an item named naughty and spice. It's just inappropriate. (I am aware there are products out there that are a lot worse) however as a Christian I just am uncomfortable promoting things that have suggestive language. Really wish they would stick with normal names.

reviews.headline: Not sure
reviews.comments: Not sure how i feel about this product, or if i got a dud. On one hand, the color (Bondi Belle) is absolutely beautiful- Its the perfect tone between contour and bronzer, and the product goes on and blends lovely. HOWEVER, the moment this arrived, it smelled like sour crayons. I had a wierd feeling about it but couldnt find anything online about the smell and figured maybe its just one of those products that doesnt smell pleasant (not everything has to smell like chocolate). In using it, it was nice enough to get through the foul smell, which did not linger once blended in. Upon use, i found my face breaking out in only the areas i used the bronzer. Thinking this could be a fluke, i stopped using it. I recently started using it again and started breaking out again. Im not sure if its the product, or if i recieved one that was expired in the first place. Either way, what a waste to have to throw it out, especially since this color is beautiful and unique.

reviews.headline: Lighter than expected
reviews.comments: This is a very pretty color. I really like the way it looks as a blush because it adds just enough color to my fair skin. The only reason I went down one star was because it actually seemed pretty pale on my lips. Great for an actual nude look though so it depends on what you're going for. I think I just needed a touch more color. Nice smooth texture and doesn't feel heavy.

reviews.headline: Perfect cream blush
reviews.comments: Salty Siren is the perfect shade and bkeds beautifully!

reviews.headline: Some of the best blush!
reviews.comments: This is the third stick I've bought of this blush. I absolutely love it! It blends so softly, it lasts all day. You can use it on your eyes or your lips if you want a matching look. I'm big for touching my face thru the day and this holds up

reviews.headline: Love the built in brush
reviews.comments: Great color, goes on smooth but it seems to take at least two applications/some building: pretty good, but not my favorite out there

reviews.headline: Don't use if you suffer from acne
reviews.comments: I really like this product, i actually own three blush stix but i just realized they are the ones giving me breakouts. I thought since it was all natural i be good but then i forgot it when i went on vacation and my zits went away. I looked into the product and realized others had had the same expirience. I reached out to the company and asked if their product was safe for acne prone skin and they just replied that the product had not beeen tested, so…..

reviews.headline: Don't use if you suffer from acne
reviews.comments: I really like this product, i actually own three blush stix but i just realized they are the ones giving me breakouts. I thought since it was all natural i be good but then i forgot it when i went on vacation and my zits went away. I looked into the product and realized others had had the same expirience. I reached out to the company and asked if their product was safe for acne prone skin and they just replied that the product had not beeen tested, so…..

reviews.headline: It's was alright
reviews.comments:
I was shopping in store, i usually just get my contour palate.
 But i saw this in store. I always heard about this brand so i wanted to give it a try. When i first used this product it took a while to blend. But at the end it blended nicely. 
About two weeks in the stick just falls out of the tube. I was sad. The price, and all its not worth it. I wouldnt get it again.

reviews.headline: Really like this product!
reviews.comments:
Love the big stick tube of color and how smoothly it applies.  Great pop of color anywhere you apply it. 
Will definitely buy again!

media.headline: I am a fan!
media.caption:
Thanks to @nudestix and @bzzagent for giving me the opportunity to try Nudies Matte Cream All Over Bronzer Stick in Bondi Belle. 

I'm usually not a fan of cream bronzing products. I find they end up feeling too heavy or greasy on my skin. They also usually emphasize my pores and finelines. But this product has changed the way I see cream products. I love that it feels super light on the skin and has a matte finish. The dual end cream/brush stick make application effortless and easy. I was actually surprised that it didn't have any silicone/dimethicone because it glides on smoothly and blended seamlessly. It also has really good color pay off and staying power even in hot weather. I only wish I got this in a color which I can also use for my lips. I love that this is a multitasking stick that can also be used on eyes and lips. This will come in super handy when I travel. I can't wait to try them in other colors!

#bronzerreview #3in1 #travelfriendly

faceoff_positive.comments: I bought this because I like creamy products for summer, and for simplicity when traveling. I am very pale and bought Naughty N Spice. I have to say, I really like this! It goes on very easily. I more tap in in several spots rather than draw a line. It blends beautifully and it lasts all day long. The brush end is great for blending, but fingers work too. It adds natural looking color to my face. I really like the look of this! There is also a good amount of product in the tube, which was nice to see.
faceoff_positive.headline: Great product!

faceoff_negative.comments: I received this product as a gift. I really like this blush stick a lot, the color is really beautiful and extremely buildable which I really enjoy for on the go or dramatic looks. The shade Bubba reminds me of a Too Faced blush that was discontinued a while ago, and it's a great alternative, especially with the ease of use without necessarily needing brushes. I find the product is a little on the dry side compared to other cream/face stick products I've used, and its a bit difficult to blend naturally. I also find that it works best as a blush as opposed to lip color, as it seems to sit on the top of the lips and looks a bit like paint. It's a nice product, but I found myself reaching for other favorites more. I do plan on continuing to use it though, because it really is such a lovely bright pink and is perfect for a pretty vibrant flushed look!
faceoff_negative.headline: Bubba - pretty color for all over, but not long lasting
